    "body": "@JanPetr This is a good idea but non easily fixable in instantsearch V1.\n\nThis has to be fixed in userland in ISV1 (like integrations are doing sometime) because the state exposed by instantsearch is not linked to the UI (stars) but to Algolia refinements semantics (here multiple numeric filters). So we have no way to know in currentRefinedValues that this is actually the star widget that constructed this refinement. See the underlying code here: https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/36bee1ef2fc54dc24d4476930f0de71e9e8f04ee/src/widgets/star-rating/star-rating.js#L170\n\nThis is getting better in react-instantsearch and is a good reminder on how the state should look like for us to be able to easily\n",
